  m_Text: "EMBERS OF THE THREE REALMS\n\nGame Design & Programming\n  1Misery1  
    \xB7   Unity 2022.3 LTS\n\n\u2014 Third-party art, audio & font \u2014\nAll gameplay
    and engine code is original. The pixel-art sprites, tiles, audio and font are
    third-party assets, used under the licenses below. Full license texts ship with
    the game in <game>_Data/StreamingAssets/ (ATTRIBUTIONS.md and licenses/).\n\n0x72
    \u2014 DungeonTileset II\n  by Robert (0x72)  \xB7  CC0 1.0\n  0x72.itch.io/dungeontileset-ii\n\nKenney
    \u2014 Roguelike / Characters / Micro / Tiny Dungeon\n  by Kenney (kenney.nl) 
    \xB7  CC0 1.0\n  kenney.nl\n\nLPC \u2014 Medieval Fantasy Character Sprites\n 
    by Johannes Sjolund (wulax); base by Stephen Challener (Redshrike)\n  CC-BY-SA
    3.0  (ShareAlike: derivatives are offered under CC-BY-SA 3.0, credit retained,
    changes stated)\n  opengameart.org/content/lpc-medieval-fantasy-character-sprites\n\nCraftPix.net
    \u2014 Free monster / swordsman packs\n  CraftPix Free License (commercial use
    & modification OK; no resale of source files; no AI/ML-training use)\n  craftpix.net/file-licenses\n\nDungeon
    Crawl Stone Soup (DCSS) tiles\n  by David E. Gervais & the DCSS team  \xB7  public
    domain / CC0\n\nArk Pixel font (Fang Zhou Pixel)\n  by TakWolf  \xB7  SIL Open
    Font License 1.1\n  github.com/TakWolf/ark-pixel-font\n\nAudio (SFX & music)\n 
    Kenney; JaggedStone; yd; MintoDog (OpenGameArt)  \xB7  CC0 1.0\n\nLicense texts
    (CC0 / CC-BY-SA 3.0 / SIL OFL 1.1 / CraftPix) are included in\nStreamingAssets/licenses/
    and ATTRIBUTIONS.md."
